history.text: Hello!
hello to you too :)
have you seen this movie before?
I think Maleficent is a decent movie.  I expected it to be a bit better, but I still like Angelina Jolie.
I thought I pick another movie but somehow we are chatting about maleficent
Angelina jolie is a great actress
so what is this movie about?
What makes it decent?
I know, I think she is beautiful (and shares a birthday with me)
It's loosely based off Sleeping Beauty.
haha for real? when is your birthday?
June 4th.
Sleeping beauty? is Angelina jolie play the sleeping beauty in this movie?
June 4th? cool, less than three more months
No she plays Maleficent, who is the main villian from sleeping beauty, and this movie shows how things transpired from her point of view.
so this movie focus on the villain point of view? cool
does it make the villain seem more decent?
and did she die at the end?

Basically she and the main guy, Stefan, get a long great as kids, but grow apart as they age, and she becomes the guardian of the moors (a magical forest), and the King tries to conquer the Moors and when she fatally wounds him the King declares whoever defeats her can marry his daughter and become heir.
Stefan visits Meleficent and tries to drug her, but can't bring himself to murder his childhood friend.

so basically the king was trying to destroy the forest which she is protecting, does not sounds like she is the bad person in this story.  he tries to drug her?  Does she have special power in this story?  Is she not a witch or something?
ah, she is the fairy
She becomes very upset by Stefan drugging her and turns the Moors into a dark kingdom and finds a raven named Diaval that's her confidant. And can transform him into different forms (such as a human.
She doesn't like Aurora, but begins to care for her when the pixies can't. And she watches over Aurora from a distance.
At 15 Aurora realizes she's being watched and begins to call Maleficent her fairy godmother.

kind of a sad stories about how a fairy and human love each other but ended up hurting each other at the end. and the princess is aurora in this story right? so what happens at the end of the story?  Did everyone get a happy ending?
so decent means not bad and worth watching but not a movie where people said it is the movie of the year right?  Maleficent looks like it got average rating for the most part.
Aurora is the princess yes, and Malefecint put a spell on her.
but maleficent does not hate the princess in this story right? She has issues with the human friend and the king but not the princess so it is different than sleeping beauty.
I believe Aurora is Stefan's child.
aurora is not the king's child?  but you said she is the princess...
she is the princess not s he is the princess
Maybe she is, it is a bit confusing.
In the long run someone tries to kiss Aurora to wake her and it doesn't work.

Anyhow, I like Angelina jolie so I would probably watch her movie just to watch her in action, or dressed up haha. I think most of movies involve her have been good and have decent stories, though an average rating is rare for movies she is in as her movie usually has higher rating.  so she was kissed but she did not wake up?  so how did she end up getting saved at the end?
Maleficent goes to Aurora's bedside, and apologizes for putting the curse on her and kisses her forehead, which awakens Aurora.

uid2response.feedback: it feels like chatting with a bot a little or someone who is not really aware of what is being said.
